The paper proposes an algorithm for building sparse decision DAGs for object detection and web page ranking, which are both topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm also involves machine learning techniques such as AdaBoost, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a single hyperparameter to control the accuracy/speed trade-off, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the algorithm for multi-class classification, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
